reviews: The most kind and amazing staff at Jo&Joe Paris Nation. So friendly and helpful from the second we arrived and throughout our whole stay. Amazing place and atmosphere and the staff is just above and beyond.

This is a fantastic hostel. Super great value!! All amenities are satisfactory. The property is well kept and clean. Beds with privacy screen are comfortable, there is linen and blanket provided, and the bathrooms/showers are clean and there is a small guest kitchen with fridge & locker storage for luggage. They offer excellent breakfast for 8€. Good mix of social and privacy. There's a bar and rooftop too! It's next to the Buzeval metro and close to the Nation & Avron Metro, so getting around the city is simple.

The staff are wonderful and attentive to the guests feel comfortable. I would stay here again, and encourage my friends to stay here too.

Best value by Paris standards. Clean, functional furnished, reasonable prices. Top service. Metro station next door. Attractive area. Restaurants, supermarkets, pubs and a parking garage nearby. Breakfast 7 Euro p.P., Snacks available until midnight.

I've had a wonderful time here. The staff was so incredibly friendly and always up for a chat. I felt so insecure about my french and had a very bad experience at the airport but at the hostel they made me feel right at home and never gave me a hard time or anything about switching to English when I ran out of words to say. The beds are comfortable and while every once in a while there will be another guest who acts a little inconsiderate, you can't stay grumpy with all the awesome people working there. It was my very first time in a place like this and I was unsure about mixed dorms before but I've always felt safe and knew there'd always be someone to talk to, if anything came up. I will be coming back for sure. Jo and Joe's is pure bliss. I even met super nice people to give me all kinds of fun tips for my trip. The bathrooms are very clean never crowded. The location is amazing as well. You have everything one could need right there. A Metro Station that takes you right into the heart of the city, a bigger station just around the corner, plenty of boulangeries with mouthwatering offers as well as several well stocked supermarkets in case you did forget to pack something or (as in my case) your suitcase takes a little longer than you to arrive. There's even a very cheap laundromat down the street to wash and dry clothing if needed. The post office across the street is also very convenient for stamps, cause while they tell you every tabak store sells them, they really don't. There's also a lot going on in the lobby area. The live music was charming, the drinks are very affordable and the food they offer is divine. The rooftop is a highlight in and of itself. I was there all by myself but never felt lonely or out of place. Thank you so very much for making my trip to Paris as awesome as it was. I was so devastated when my luggage was lost on my way there but you guys saved the day and made my week so very relaxed and comfortable. I unfortunately didn't get to take one of their supposedly amazing city tours since I didn't know they offered them and had very busy mornings planned beforehand but I will make damn sure to take part in one next time I stay there! You guys rock!

We had an amazing time. The staff were so lovely and here 24/7. Comfy bed, safe and secure rooms, clean bathroom. Luggage storage came in handy. Right beside the metro station. Would recommend to a friend.

8-bed shared-room with modern bunks (orientable reading light, 2 USB connectors, privacy screens on lower bunks). Great showers. Restaurant/bar/lounge on ground floor very comfortable and cosy (nice and warm inside on a freezing winter's day). Staff friendly and helpful.

My stay there went absolutely great !
Everything was very clean which was very appreciable, especially the showers (except for the traditionnal gifts left by my fellow travellers such as hair). The room was also quite big, which really surprised me. I also really appreciated the cosy room with a fridge and microwave put to our disposal, very useful and practical for those who stay for quite a long time and who can't afford to go the restaurant every night.
Finally, everyone working there was absolutely nice and was always happy to answer our questions.

Was there anything negative?
My only negative thought goes to the fact that I was on the top bed in my shared room. In a general way, they are WAY less convenient than the lower beds. It wouldn't have bothered me if I had stayed for a day or two, but I stayed for an entire week and it became quite tiring.
- In the lower beds you have this kind of screen you can pull that is very opaque to isolate yourself ,so you can't see the light outside of your little "bubble". There is absolutely nothing to hide yourself from the light in the top beds, (added to the fact that the lights are about 30 cm over your head).
- It also bothered me to constanly go back and forth on the little ladder everytime I wanted to do something. Again it wouldn't have bothered me for a day or two, but a week is way longer.

Overall my stay was really cool, thanks guys !!

Excellent hostel experience for travelers. They had a great staff (esp. Merita), central location near many fun things to do, and a convivial atmosphere. Rooms were reasonably priced. Would highly recommend!

Shared a bedroom with 5 other girls. They were all very respectful and the atmosphere was quite nice.
Whole place is super clean and modern, everything was working correctly and i didn’t lack anything.
Well located, neighbourhood is okay and accessible.
Very good price for that accommodation!
Breakfast is also super good and quite cheap.

Had a three-night stay here with a friend from college. Every employee was so nice, especially Merita and Ornella!

Great food as well.

Rooftop is beautiful, and the common room is full of travelers, local Parisians, artists, and other interesting people. Kind of weirdly happening, all in this one place!

I really loved the place . It was clean , enough spacious and moreover the hostel is next to the metro station and shops. It was very convinient for me to visit many places because of ease of metro access.

Overall, the stay was nice and the room we had was great for a group of 3 friends. However, sometimes a bit lacking in a few things: No handtowels, only two hooks in the bathroom (in a 3-bed room), and the lighting situation is quite bad. Also a bit of a weird smell in the hallway and coming from the shower drain.

I stayed at the hosyel with my family for 5 days.
The hostel was better than a hotel, truly clean, with the greatest staff. Special thanks to Ornella and Patricia, who were always wonderful, kind to us, really the best! I honestly recommend it.
Great energy, great prople, great place!

Stayed here for 5 nights with two teenagers. The place was very clean and spacious comparing to many other options. We had a room for 3 persons, our own big toilet and shower. Personnel was very kind and helpful. Area itself had a minimarket and many bakeries, I recommend bakery called 57 just around the corner. Metrostation (Buzenval) almost next to hostel so it was easy to Explore Paris all around. Overall very satisfied and will stay in the same place next time.

The location of the Nation hostel is great, with the metro line 9 within 20 meters, and Nation metro station within a 10min walk, making central Paris very accessible.
The staff were very kind and accommodating, particularly Ornella who genuinely seemed happy to be there and welcome guests.
The rooms and bathrooms were clean.
The lower bunks have privacy screens which can be pulled down to make the bed completely private - a huge benefit in a hostel.
My only point to note is that the storage lockers are smaller than I have encountered at other hostels, so just be aware that if you have a large bag you may have to keep it in the room with you, not locked away (although I had no issues doing this).
I would be happy to stay at this hostel again.

One of the best hostel I’ve stayed in Europe! The staffs were extremely friendly, kind and welcoming, the people there really made it feel like home. Would 100% stay there again when I’m in next time.

The staff were very welcoming and friendly, especially Victor, who seemed very knowledgeable and passionate about his job. The drinks at the bar were of good quality and well worth the money. We stayed for 2 nights and we enjoyed both and encountered no obstacles.Thank you for having us!

The staff are lovely, the dorm was spacious and well appointed. The linen looked clean as did the bathroom (also spacious), so great potential, but BED BUGS! The reception next morning was apologetic when I showed my myriad bites up and down my arms, legs, face and back. I am still trying not to scratch. The rooms need steam cleaning and mattresses replaced.

Great staff, great quality hostel, great rooms a lot better than a average hostel. Easy to get to the hostel on trains or scooters ( would recommend scooters in Paris) so you can see more of it. Would come back for sure. Food was good too.

The hostel is close to a metro station and so it’s easy to access everything. The staff was nice, it’s easy to meet new people from all over the world in the bar and roof top.

You feel safe and all is clean and you can even eat there. No reason not to recommend it :)

I only stayed one night so can't comment much as I also got in late because of delays. What I will say is lovely staff, great breakfast, excellent powerful and clean showers and a comfy bed. Rooftop is also lovely.

Was great to arrive and have a late lunch on the rooftop while waiting for our room to be cleaned ! The staff were super nice and friendly. went to see a concert and when we came back there was a dj playing some nice music and we enjoyed a drink before going to bed. Even though we stayed one night our experience was great

It was very clean, good bed, wifi and everything you need, friendly staff, quiet, clean showers and toilets, location is okay, store around the corner.

Only a place for cooking could have made it 100% instead of 95% but would def go back and recommend it!

disappointed with the cleaning of the room. Also, the sheets were not on the bed when we arrived (you have to make your own bed). Low price-quality relationship. It was not bad, but for the price, I expected more.

The stay was really nice. The room was good and the stuff is very friendly. The rooftop is quite cool but closes quite early. The breakfast is very plain and bit expensive for what you get. Also the bathroom was not sooo clean. I’m general it was a really nice stay.

The staff was once again very friendly, the atmosphere is also very nice and the location is very convenient.
Nice to see small improvements made to the the bunk bed concept (some plastic retainers have been added to prevent the shed thread.)

The hostel is very modern, confortable and accessible. There is a Metro station 1 minute away that takes you everywhere in Paris. It is not in the center, but you can get there easilly in 30/40 minutes.

Actually i was not happy to be there for a reasons :
This reasons i‘m talking about comparing with other hostels as the same price .
1) Very Poor breakfast , and long waiting time on the queue .
2) i have ordered an iron and they told me there is no iron .
3) there are no lights in the room and i always using the flash phone of mine even in the afternoon .
4) 3 times during 20 hours there was no paper toilet in the toilet , and i go to the reception to put some toilet paper which she really did it immediately and she apologised to me ,i would thank her .
5) normally there is always a towel in the other hostels but there was no , i have asked the reception for a towel , she said 4 Euro sir , i said whaaaat ,,even that the towel is to bad quality and i don‘t know if they washed or not because there was a smell , i took it but i didn‘t use it .
6) in room 101 first floor , thers is a heavy sound i don’t know what was it ,which we get up 3-4 times between 12am and 6:00am and it was super high sound .

Nice concept, but the experience really depends on the bunk bed you get: lower bed with shades is great, upper beds: the light is directed in your face.
This time I was unlucky: upper bunk bed and not very respectful people switching on the light at 2:30am, in top of speaking loud...

I’m in love with this place. The bed is comfortable, shower is amazing, great breakfast, best staff and everything else is so modern, clean and cool. Also the location is perfect. I’m absolutely positive that I will come back again to stay there.

I went to Paris on my own, and stayed in a 6 bed female room. Everything was good! The room was spacious and clean, the bed was confortable and wide. The bathrooms are Also clean, there is no trouble with Hot Water, and you have room to leave your things close to you while you shower. The easthetic of the place Is amazing. They have a beautiful terrace (I didn't use It but just checked it out), with a bar and DJ sometimes. The vibes are great, there is always many Young people around. There is Also a "Happy House" fully equiped with everything you need to eat your own food, and sofá, cushions as well. The breakfast is really cheap and for the price, it's really complete. The staff was super kind, they are always willing to help you. The hotel is well located and well connected by metro or bus. I would definetely recommend to stay here.

Its 100% a youth hostel. If you are young or want to party and you dont need a lot of sleep and dont have young kids, its just a perfect place. If you want to rest, to sleep at night and want some comfort, dont go here. Was reasonably priced, at 50m of a metro at 30minutes from the city center.

This was my first trip to Paris and my first stay in a hostel. The hostel was welcoming on arrival, the staff were super friendly. Our room was warm and cosy and after spending our days venturing around Paris, we slept very well! The room didn’t have a hairdryer but you just ask one of the staff at reception and they can provide you with one once you give a deposit. It was also very safe, the floors that the rooms were on couldn’t be accessed without a room key. So visitors couldn’t come near the rooms. I am unsure of what the food is like as we ate out everyday but the bar was very busy in the evening when they held events. The hostel is located right beside a Metro stop so it was very easy to get around Paris. I would definitely stay here again!

Very nice atmosphere. Although beds are small, but ita a fun experience.
Some issues are there regarding cleaning of rooms, but still bedsheets and bedcovers are nice and clean. I recommended all to try this property. This is an excellent property for solo travellers and for those who wish to travel in low budget in Paris.

I booked for a different date, the website put a random date and I tried reaching out to the reception with no response. Nobody helped me so I paid for nights I did not even use. I paid for more nights than needed. So it really sucks that they do not want to help their own customers just to keep the money :)

The worst part is that I wanted to stay a whole month with them and now that I saw the intentions and ZERO will to help me I decided to book somewhere else.

Also, it is super stupid that they do not allow people to eat almost in any place, just a dirty tiny kitchen that was too dirty to enjoy.

I checked out at 5 am because I had a flight and I had to wait because there was no one in there.

it does not have any kitchen!!!!! you can not cook there!! just a table, fridge and microwave

Has a good offer of food, events and the venue is very comfortable and cosy. It was easy to get their from the station and its not too far from the shops. It was very clean and my room was nice. The only thing I would improve is what you get for your money

One of the best hostels i ve been great price really good and confy beds and great location close to metro supermarkets,bistros and everything.And also the whole place was crazy beautiful inside......

It was awful. I know it’s a matter of taste but it feels like a room can be hosed down: every thing is either absent or securely fastened to the wall.
The beds are small, short and have some plastic cover which makes you sweat during the night. That wil make you awake. If you need a midnight pee, be prepared to look straight into so much light, so be nearly blinded. Now you are full awake. And in the morning, around 5 there is so much noise on the street you can conclude you barely slept.
Also, you cannot eat or drink in your room, wtf?

Not the best quality - price.
Between 28/32€ for a 8 mixed bedroom doorm without breakfast.
This pricerange is only for hispters wanting to try a fancy hostel, not for adventurous backpackers.
Plus, unfortunately as every youth hotel in Paris they don't have a kitchen so you need to pay your food way more expensive than usual cause you can't cook.
Paris hospitality...
You have to note they have a room in the basement with a fridge and microwaves, at least that's something.
Also, it's personal of course but I find this hostel way to dark, in the room, bathroom, downstairs bars. The only real light you get is on the rooftop, if not raining.
For the rest, it's brandnew with capsule beds, that good.
Cleaningness can be improved as well.

The stuff is friendly and helpful. Rooms are clean and modern, big beds and it was very comfortable to sleep. There is youth atmosphere, chilling zones and WiFi everywhere. I liked it. I had no credit card to use, but we found the solution.

I've been staying there twice already and it's really nice ! The staff is super nice, helping and welcoming. The place is alive, with music nights and a bar on the rooftop.
The rooms are well thought, really clean and comfy as well. I would definitely recommend this hostel for short or long stay !!❤️
